# FocusBot CSS Rules

Applies when editing any `.css` file (extension UI).

## Primary goals

- **No duplicated CSS**: do not introduce duplicate selectors or duplicated declarations across files.
- **No unintended overrides**: add styles in a way that does not change existing UI unless explicitly requested.
- **Match FocusBot desktop aesthetic**: dark, glassy materials, clear elevation, subtle borders, strong focus states.

## Workflow (mandatory)

- **Before adding a selector**: scan the target CSS file to ensure the selector (or an equivalent one) does not already exist.
- **Before adding a new rule**: check whether an existing utility/component class can be reused instead.
- **If a selector already exists**:
  - Prefer **editing the existing block** rather than adding a second block for the same selector.
  - If you need a variant, add a **new class** (e.g. `.component--variant`) instead of increasing specificity.

## Scoping & architecture

- **Scope new page styles under a wrapper** (e.g. `.settings-page ...`) to avoid leaking into other surfaces.
- Prefer **component/page-prefixed classes** (BEM-ish):
  - `.settings-section`, `.settings-section-title`, `.settings-radio-card`, `.settings-radio-card-desc`
- Avoid global element selectors for styling (e.g. `div`, `span`, `p`) unless it is a truly global base style.
- Keep specificity low:
  - Prefer `.class` over `main .class` over `.outer .inner .class`.
  - Avoid `!important` except as a last resort to fix third-party/UA behavior; document why in the PR description (not in CSS).

## Design alignment (desktop app → extension)

The desktop app uses a **3 elevation layer** structure and glassy materials. Mirror that in extension CSS:

- **3 surface layers**: page (darkest) < column/section < card (lightest).
- **Dark palette guidance** (use as inspiration; keep consistent across the page):
  - Page: `#110E1A` / `#0f1220`-like
  - Section: `#1C1730`-like
  - Card: `#2A2242`-like
- **Borders**: subtle 1px borders with low-alpha white (e.g. `rgba(255,255,255,0.08–0.18)`).
- **Corner radius**: Small 6px, Medium 10px, Large 12px.
- **Focus**: always provide visible focus indicators (`:focus-visible` / `:focus-within`) with an accent outline.
- **Meaning**: never encode meaning with color alone (pair with text/labels).

Prefer using **CSS variables** for the page/module to keep consistent color + elevation:

- Define variables on the page wrapper, e.g. `.settings-page { --surface-1: ...; --surface-2: ...; }`
- Use variables instead of repeating raw hex values.

## “Don’t overwrite older styles” guardrails

- Do not change shared/base selectors (e.g. `body`, `button`, `input`, `.card`) unless the user explicitly requested a global redesign.
- Prefer additive classes and wrapper scoping over overrides.
- If you must override existing behavior:
  - Scope it under a wrapper (`.settings-page .card { ... }`)
  - Keep the change minimal and localized
  - Avoid relying on cascade order across multiple files

## Quick checklist before finishing

- [ ] No duplicate selectors were added.
- [ ] New styles are scoped (wrapper + component classes).
- [ ] Specificity is minimal (no deep selector chains).
- [ ] Focus states are visible.
- [ ] Colors/elevation feel consistent with FocusBot desktop (3 layers, subtle borders, glassy feel).
